         <div type="translation" resp="#jmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Sacred</supplied> to the gods below of Balyna; she lived for thirty-eight years; Caius Caecilius Lupus had this made for his most obedient wife and for the builder.</p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
        <!--   <p>The stone is said by Dr. C. Chiesa to come either from the Garian massif or from the
               area of Beni Ulid in the Orfella. Its findspot was probably not its original position
               - there were a few large stones nearby, but no sign of other dressed blocks.</p>
            <p>Line 2. For this name cf. Baline at Cirta, <title level="m">CIL</title> VIII, 7827.</p>
            <p>Line 6. <foreign>Structori</foreign> presumably refers to the builder, C. Caecilius Lupus.</p>  --> 
